
1. What is Power BI and why is it used?

Power BI enables non-technical users to create professional dashboards from diverse data sources (Excel, SQL, APIs). Used by 85% of Fortune 500 companies for KPI tracking, sales analysis, and executive reporting.​

Primary Use Cases:

    Sales performance dashboards

    HR attrition analysis

    Financial forecasting

    Supply chain monitoring



2. Explain the Power BI workflow.


1. Connect → Excel, SQL, APIs, web
2. Transform → Power Query (cleaning)
3. Model → Relationships + DAX measures  
4. Visualize → Reports (multi-page)
5. Pin → Dashboard (single page overview)
6. Share → Power BI Service + Apps

