3. What is Power Query used for?

Power Query handles ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) with no-code interface:

| Function  | Example                   |
| --------- | ------------------------- |
| Clean     | Remove duplicates, nulls  |
| Transform | Split columns, pivot data |
| Merge     | Join Excel + SQL tables   |
| Schedule  | Daily refresh automation  |

M Code Example:


// Remove null salaries + promote headers
Table.SelectRows(Source, each [Salary] <> null)
Table.PromoteHeaders(_, [PromotedHeaders=true])



4. Difference between report and dashboard in Power BI.

| Feature       | Report                     | Dashboard                         |
| ------------- | -------------------------- | --------------------------------- |
| Pages         | Multi-page analysis        | Single page overview newhorizons​ |
| Edit          | Power BI Desktop           | Power BI Service (pin only)       |
| Interactivity | Full (drill-down, slicers) | Limited (tiles only)              |
| Data Source   | Single dataset             | Multiple reports                  |
| Audience      | Analysts (deep dive)       | Executives (KPI glance)           |

Production Strategy: Reports → Detailed analysis | Dashboards → Executive summary.



5. How does data modeling help in Power BI?

Data modeling creates semantic layer with relationships + DAX measures:


Raw Tables → Star Schema → Fast queries + Reusable metrics

Key Benefits:


✅ Single source of truth (no Excel chaos)
✅ Reusable measures (Sales YOY, Attrition Rate)
✅ Fast performance (1M+ rows)
✅ Role-based security (Finance sees revenue only)

DAX Example:


// Reusable measure across all visuals
Total Salary = SUM(Employees[Salary])
YOY Growth = 
DIVIDE(
    [Total Salary] - CALCULATE([Total Salary], SAMEPERIODLASTYEAR('Date'[Date])),
    CALCULATE([Total Salary], SAMEPERIODLASTYEAR('Date'[Date]))
)

